13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1501 of Title 60, unless there
16 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 Solar energy and industrial battery storage facilities,
18 excluding residential solar energy panels, shall have the following
19 setback requirements:
20 1. Shall not be located within five hundred (500) feet of an
21 occupied structure or occupied residence unless waived in writing by
22 the owner of the structure or residence;
23 2. Shall not be located within one hundred (100) feet of any
24 outer boundary of the facility property; and
Req. No. 12481 Page 1

1 3. Shall not be located within one hundred (100) feet from any
2 public road right-of-way.
3 4. Shall not be located within one and one-half (1 1/2) miles
4 from the centerline of any airport, public school, or hospital.
5 5. Shall not be located within two (2) miles from a wildlife
6 refuge, wildlife management area, or any body of water used by
7 migratory waterfowl.
8 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
